
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-cantor-ietf-sasl-saml-ec-00.txt'>
    <title>"A SASL Mechanism for SAML Enhanced Clients", Scott Cantor</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-cantor-ietf-sasl-saml-ec-00.txt</link>
    <description>Security Assertion Markup Language (SAML) 2.0 is a generalized framework for the exchange of security-related information between asserting and relying parties.  Simple Authentication and Security Layer (SASL) is an application framework to facilitate an extensible authentication model.  This document specifies a SASL mechanism for SAML 2.0 that leverages the capabilities of a SAML- aware "enhanced client" to address significant barriers to federated authentication in a manner that encourages reuse of existing SAML bindings and profiles designed for non-browser scenarios.</description>
    <dc:date>2010-05-26T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
